<REFENTRY id="echo">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>
echo
</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>
<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>echo</REFNAME>
<REFPURPOSE>
display a line of text
</REFPURPOSE>
</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<SYNOPSIS>
echo [STRING]... 
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
Unlike the behavior specified in the SUS, whether <COMMAND>echo</COMMAND>
supports options is implementation defined.  Applications should not
run <COMMAND>echo</COMMAND> with a first argument starting with a hyphen,
or with any arguments containing backslashes; they should use
<COMMAND>printf</COMMAND> in those cases.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>
</REFENTRY>
